/-!
# Codes for positive inductive-recursive definitions

`IR I O` is the type of codes for inductive-recursive definitions with
input index type `I` and output index type `O`, presented as the W-type
of a polynomial functor `IR.pFunctor I O` whose shapes are the three
code constructors ÔÇö constant (`iota`), dependent sum (`sigma`), and
dependent product (`delta`) ÔÇö and whose directions are their subcode
arities. A code is interpreted as a functor from the free coproduct
completion of `I` to that of `O` (both treated as discrete categories,
`CategoryTheory.FreeCoprodCompDisc`, the category of families of
elements of the index type): this file constructs the object map and
morphism map of the interpretation.
It follows [GhaniNordvallForsbergMalatesta2015], Section 2
(Definitions 2.1ÔÇô2.2, Theorem 2.4, and Examples 2.5ÔÇô2.6), which
presents the codes of [DybjerSetzer1999] and the functorial semantics
of [DybjerSetzer2003]. The split into separate input and output index
types ÔÇö generalizing the single shared index type of
[DybjerSetzer1999] and [DybjerSetzer2003] ÔÇö follows Definition 3 of
[HancockMcBrideGhaniMalatestaAltenkirch2013], whose footnote observes
that the generalization allows the construction of partial fixed
points.

## Main definitions

* `IR.pFunctor` ÔÇö the polynomial functor whose W-type defines codes:
  shapes `IR.Shape`, directions `IR.Direction`.
* `IR.Dest`, `IR.Dest.elim`, `IR.Dest.elimInv`, `IR.destEquiv` ÔÇö the
  pattern-matched destructor for morphisms out of `IR.Obj`, its
  conversions to and from such morphisms, and the equivalence they
  form.
* `IR.DepDest`, `IR.DepDest.elim`, `IR.DepDest.elimInv`,
  `IR.depDestEquiv` ÔÇö the dependent counterparts.
* `IR.objIota`, `IR.objSigma`, `IR.objDelta` ÔÇö the element
  constructors of `IR.Obj`, one per shape.
* `IR`, `IR.mk` ÔÇö the type of codes and its constructor.
* `IR.iota`, `IR.sigma`, `IR.delta` ÔÇö the code constructors, one per
  shape.
* `IR.elim`, `IR.rec` ÔÇö the eliminator and the dependent recursor,
  the latter with step arguments of type `IR.RecStep` (the `Type`
  specialization, alongside `IR.InductionStep` for `Prop`, of the
  `Sort`-valued `IR.Step`).
* `IR.interpObj`, `IR.interpMor` ÔÇö the object map and morphism map of
  the interpretation of an `IR` code as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map` (a
  functor between the free coproduct completions of `I` and `O`).
* `univCode`, `univEndo`, `univEndoMor` ÔÇö the code of the universe
  generated by an arbitrary family of starting types and closed under
  dependent sums and dependent products, with the object and morphism
  maps of its interpretation.

## Main statements

* `IR.ext`, `IR.snd_eq_of_eq` ÔÇö extensionality for codes.
* `IR.induction` ÔÇö the induction principle, the recursor restricted to
  `Prop`-valued motives.

## Implementation notes

The interpretation is given by its object map (`IR.interpObj`) and
its morphism map (`IR.interpMor`); the functor laws (preservation of
identities and composition, completing Theorem 2.4 of
[GhaniNordvallForsbergMalatesta2015]) are not yet stated. Neither is
the propositional computation rule of `IR.rec`, which would
characterize `IR.interpMor` at each code constructor. The initial
algebras of the interpreted endofunctors ÔÇö the universes the codes
describe, in the endofunctor case `IR I I` ÔÇö are not constructed
here; the set-theoretic model of [DybjerSetzer2003] justifies their
existence using a Mahlo cardinal.

The sigma and delta arities of `IR.Shape` share the single universe
`uA`, following the single `Set` of Definition 2.1. The output index
type `O` parameterizes the `iota` shapes (a code `IR.iota I O o`
decodes to `o : O`); the input index type `I` parameterizes the
`delta` directions (a code `IR.delta I O A c` receives the decodings
of its recursive arguments as assignments `A Ôćĺ I`).

The whole file is exposed (`@[expose] public section`): downstream
modules, in particular the tests, rely on definitional reduction
through every definition here.

## References

* [DybjerSetzer1999]
* [DybjerSetzer2003]
* [GhaniNordvallForsbergMalatesta2015]
* [HancockMcBrideGhaniMalatestaAltenkirch2013]

## Tags

inductive-recursive, polynomial functor, W-type, universe, container
-/

@[expose] public section

universe uA uI uO

namespace IndRec

open CategoryTheory

variable (I : Type uI) (O : Type uO)

namespace IR

/-- The shape type of the polynomial functor whose W-type defines
codes for positive inductive-recursive types. -/
def Shape : Type (max (uA + 1) uO) :=
  O ÔŐĽ Type uA ÔŐĽ Type uA

/-- The direction type of the polynomial functor whose W-type defines
codes for positive inductive-recursive types. -/
def Direction : Shape.{uA, uO} O Ôćĺ Type (max uA uI) :=
  Sum.elim (fun _ ÔćŽ PEmpty)
    (Sum.elim (fun A ÔćŽ ULift.{uI} A) (fun A ÔćŽ A Ôćĺ I))

/-- Simplification for the constant (`iota`) case of `IR.Direction`. -/
@[simp]
theorem direction_iota (o : O) : Direction.{uA, uI, uO} I O (Sum.inl o) = PEmpty := rfl

/-- Simplification for the dependent sum (`sigma`) case of
`IR.Direction`. -/
@[simp]
theorem direction_sigma (A : Type uA) :
    Direction.{uA, uI, uO} I O (Sum.inr (Sum.inl A)) = ULift.{uI} A := rfl

/-- Simplification for the dependent product (`delta`) case of
`IR.Direction`. -/
@[simp]
theorem direction_delta (A : Type uA) :
    Direction.{uA, uI, uO} I O (Sum.inr (Sum.inr A)) = (A Ôćĺ I) := rfl

/-- Rewrite the direction type along a shape-type equality. -/
def directionOfEq {s s' : Shape.{uA, uO} O} : s = s' Ôćĺ Direction I O s Ôćĺ Direction I O s'
  | rfl => id

/-- Elimination rule for `IR.Direction`. -/
def directionElim.{v} (V : Type v) (¤â : (A : Type uA) Ôćĺ A Ôćĺ V)
    (╬┤ : (A : Type uA) Ôćĺ (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ V) (s : Shape O) (ds : Direction I O s) : V :=
  match s with
  | Sum.inl _ => PEmpty.elim ds
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inl (A : Type uA)) => ¤â A (ULift.down ds)
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inr (A : Type uA)) => ╬┤ A ds

/-- The polynomial functor whose W-type defines codes for positive
inductive-recursive types. -/
def pFunctor : PFunctor.{max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI} :=
  ÔčĘShape O, Direction I OÔčę

/-- The value at `V` of the interpretation of `IR.pFunctor` as an
endofunctor on `Type`. -/
def Obj.{v} (V : Type v) : Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO v) :=
  PFunctor.Obj.{v, max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI} (pFunctor I O) V

/-- The first component of `IR.Obj`. -/
def ObjFst : Type (max (uA + 1) uO) :=
  Shape.{uA, uO} O

/-- The second component of `IR.Obj`. -/
def ObjSnd.{v} (V : Type v) : ObjFst O Ôćĺ Type (max uA uI v) :=
  fun s ÔćŽ Direction.{uA, uI, uO} I O s Ôćĺ V

/-- Rewrite the second component of `IR.Obj` along a shape-type
equality. -/
def objSndOfEq.{v} (V : Type v) {s s' : ObjFst.{uA, uO} O} :
    s = s' Ôćĺ ObjSnd I O V s Ôćĺ ObjSnd I O V s'
  | rfl => id

/-- The constant (`iota`) element constructor of `IR.Obj`: shape `o`,
no directions. -/
def objIota.{v} (V : Type v) (o : O) : Obj.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V :=
  ÔčĘSum.inl o, PEmpty.elimÔčę

/-- The dependent sum (`sigma`) element constructor of `IR.Obj`: shape
`A`, directions assigned by `f` (through the lifted direction type
`ULift A`). -/
def objSigma.{v} (V : Type v) (A : Type uA) (f : A Ôćĺ V) :
    Obj.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V :=
  ÔčĘSum.inr (Sum.inl A), f Ôłś ULift.downÔčę

/-- The dependent product (`delta`) element constructor of `IR.Obj`:
shape `A`, directions assigned by `f`. -/
def objDelta.{v} (V : Type v) (A : Type uA) (f : (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ V) :
    Obj.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V :=
  ÔčĘSum.inr (Sum.inr A), fÔčę

/-- Every element of `IR.Obj` with an `iota` shape equals the
`IR.objIota` element: direction assignments out of the empty direction
type are all equal. -/
theorem objIota_eq_mk.{v} (V : Type v) (o : O)
    (ds : Direction.{uA, uI, uO} I O (Sum.inl o) Ôćĺ V) :
    objIota I O V o = (ÔčĘSum.inl o, dsÔčę : Obj.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V) :=
  congrArg (Sigma.mk (Sum.inl o)) (funext (fun x ÔćŽ PEmpty.elim x))

/-- A destructor for `IR.Obj` ÔÇö a pattern-matched form of
elimination. -/
def Dest.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w) : Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO v w) :=
  (O Ôćĺ W) ├Ś ((A : Type uA) Ôćĺ (A Ôćĺ V) Ôćĺ W) ├Ś ((A : Type uA) Ôćĺ ((A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ V) Ôćĺ W)

/-- Convert `IR.Dest` to a morphism out of `IR.Obj` (an eliminator). -/
def Dest.elim.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w)
    (dest : Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W) : Obj I O V Ôćĺ W :=
  fun ÔčĘs, dsÔčę ÔćŽ match s with
  | Sum.inl o => dest.1 o
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inl (A : Type uA)) => dest.2.1 A (ds Ôłś ULift.up)
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inr (A : Type uA)) => dest.2.2 A ds

/-- The inverse of `IR.Dest.elim`. -/
def Dest.elimInv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w) (m : Obj I O V Ôćĺ W) :
    Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W :=
  ÔčĘfun o ÔćŽ m (objIota I O V o),
    fun A f ÔćŽ m (objSigma I O V A f),
    fun A f ÔćŽ m (objDelta I O V A f)Ôčę

/-- `IR.Dest.elimInv` is a left inverse of `IR.Dest.elim`. -/
theorem Dest.elimInv_elim.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w)
    (dest : Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W) :
    Dest.elimInv.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W (Dest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W dest) =
      dest :=
  rfl

/-- `IR.Dest.elimInv` is a right inverse of `IR.Dest.elim`. -/
theorem Dest.elim_elimInv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w)
    (m : Obj I O V Ôćĺ W) :
    Dest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W (Dest.elimInv.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W m) = m :=
  funext <| fun ÔčĘs, dsÔčę ÔćŽ match s with
  | Sum.inl o => congrArg m (objIota_eq_mk.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V o ds)
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inl _) => rfl
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inr _) => rfl

/-- `IR.Dest` is equivalent to the morphisms out of `IR.Obj`. -/
def destEquiv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Type w) :
    Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W Ôëâ (Obj I O V Ôćĺ W) where
  toFun := Dest.elim I O V W
  invFun := Dest.elimInv I O V W
  left_inv := Dest.elimInv_elim I O V W
  right_inv := Dest.elim_elimInv I O V W

/-- A dependent destructor for `IR.Obj` ÔÇö a pattern-matched form of
elimination. -/
def DepDest.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO v w) :=
  ((o : O) Ôćĺ W (objIota I O V o)) ├Ś
    ((A : Type uA) Ôćĺ (f : A Ôćĺ V) Ôćĺ W (objSigma I O V A f)) ├Ś
    ((A : Type uA) Ôćĺ (f : (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ V) Ôćĺ W (objDelta I O V A f))

/-- Convert `IR.DepDest` to a destructor into a sigma type. -/
def sigmaDest.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W Ôćĺ
      Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, max (uA + 1) uI uO v w} I O V (╬ú e, W e) :=
  fun dest ÔćŽ
    ÔčĘfun o ÔćŽ ÔčĘobjIota I O V o, dest.1 oÔčę,
      fun A f ÔćŽ ÔčĘobjSigma I O V A f, dest.2.1 A fÔčę,
      fun A f ÔćŽ ÔčĘobjDelta I O V A f, dest.2.2 A fÔčęÔčę

/-- Convert `IR.DepDest` to a morphism into a sigma type. -/
def sigmaElim.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W Ôćĺ Obj I O V Ôćĺ ╬ú e, W e :=
  Dest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, max (uA + 1) uI uO v w} I O V (╬ú e, W e) Ôłś
    sigmaDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W

/-- `IR.sigmaElim` is a section of the first projection. -/
theorem sigmaElim_fst.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w)
    (dest : DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W) (e : Obj I O V) :
    (sigmaElim I O V W dest e).1 = e :=
  match e with
  | ÔčĘs, dsÔčę => match s with
    | Sum.inl o => objIota_eq_mk.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V o ds
    | Sum.inr (Sum.inl _) => rfl
    | Sum.inr (Sum.inr _) => rfl

/-- Convert `IR.DepDest` to a dependent eliminator for `IR.Obj`. -/
def DepDest.elim.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W Ôćĺ (e : Obj I O V) Ôćĺ W e :=
  fun dest ÔćŽ
    sigmaFstSectionElim (sigmaElim I O V W dest) (sigmaElim_fst I O V W dest)

/-- The inverse of `IR.DepDest.elim`. -/
def DepDest.elimInv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    ((e : Obj I O V) Ôćĺ W e) Ôćĺ DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W :=
  fun m ÔćŽ
    ÔčĘfun o ÔćŽ m (objIota I O V o),
      fun A f ÔćŽ m (objSigma I O V A f),
      fun A f ÔćŽ m (objDelta I O V A f)Ôčę

/-- `IR.DepDest.elimInv` is a left inverse of `IR.DepDest.elim`. -/
theorem DepDest.elimInv_elim.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w)
    (dest : DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W) :
    DepDest.elimInv.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W
      (DepDest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W dest) = dest :=
  rfl

/-- `IR.DepDest.elimInv` is a right inverse of `IR.DepDest.elim`. -/
theorem DepDest.elim_elimInv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w)
    (m : (e : Obj I O V) Ôćĺ W e) :
    DepDest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W
      (DepDest.elimInv.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W m) = m :=
  funext <| fun ÔčĘs, dsÔčę ÔćŽ match s with
  | Sum.inl o => objIota_eq_mk.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V o ds ÔľŞ rfl
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inl _) => rfl
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inr _) => rfl

/-- `IR.DepDest` is equivalent to the dependent eliminators of
`IR.Obj`. -/
def depDestEquiv.{v, w} (V : Type v) (W : Obj I O V Ôćĺ Type w) :
    DepDest.{uA, uI, uO, v, w} I O V W Ôëâ ((e : Obj I O V) Ôćĺ W e) where
  toFun := DepDest.elim I O V W
  invFun := DepDest.elimInv I O V W
  left_inv := DepDest.elimInv_elim I O V W
  right_inv := DepDest.elim_elimInv I O V W

/-- A pattern-matched form of an algebra of `IR.pFunctor`. -/
def Alg.{v} (V : Type v) : Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO v) :=
  Dest.{uA, uI, uO, v, v} I O V V

/-- Convert `IR.Alg` to the morphism form of an algebra of
`IR.pFunctor`. -/
def Alg.toHom.{v} (V : Type v) (alg : Alg.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V) : Obj I O V Ôćĺ V :=
  Dest.elim.{uA, uI, uO, v, v} I O V V alg

end IR

/-- The type of codes for positive inductive-recursive definitions:
the W-type of `IR.pFunctor`. -/
def IR : Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO) :=
  PFunctor.W.{max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI} (IR.pFunctor I O)

namespace IR

/-- The constructor for `IR`. -/
def mk (s : Shape O) (d : Direction I O s Ôćĺ IR I O) : IR I O :=
  WType.mk.{max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI} s d

/-- The constant (`iota`) code: no subcodes; its interpretation is the
constant functor at the object with one name decoding to `o`. -/
def iota (o : O) : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O :=
  mk I O (Sum.inl o) PEmpty.elim

/-- The dependent sum (`sigma`) code: subcodes `c` indexed by `A`
(through the lifted direction type `ULift A`); its interpretation is
the pointwise indexed coproduct over `A` of the interpretations of the
subcodes. -/
def sigma (A : Type uA) (c : ULift.{uI} A Ôćĺ IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O) : IR I O :=
  mk I O (Sum.inr (Sum.inl A)) c

/-- The dependent product (`delta`) code: subcodes `c` indexed by the
assignments of decodings to `A`; its interpretation takes recursive
arguments indexed by `A` and passes their decodings to `c`. -/
def delta (A : Type uA) (c : (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O) : IR I O :=
  mk I O (Sum.inr (Sum.inr A)) c

/-- Congruence for `IR.mk` in the direction assignment. -/
theorem mk_congr (s : Shape O) {ds ds' : Direction I O s Ôćĺ IR I O} :
    ds = ds' Ôćĺ mk.{uA, uI, uO} I O s ds = mk.{uA, uI, uO} I O s ds'
  | rfl => rfl

/-- The motive of the proof of `IR.ext`. -/
def ExtMotive (s : Shape.{uA, uO} O) (d : Direction I O s Ôćĺ IR I O)
    (s' : Shape O) (eq1 : s = s') : Prop :=
  ÔłÇ d' : Direction I O s' Ôćĺ IR I O, d = d' Ôłś directionOfEq I O eq1 Ôćĺ mk I O s d = mk I O s' d'

/-- Extensionality for `IR` (equality is determined by equality of
shapes and pointwise equality of directions). -/
theorem ext {ir ir' : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O} (eq1 : ir.1 = ir'.1)
    (eq2 : ir.2 = ir'.2 Ôłś directionOfEq I O eq1) : ir = ir' :=
  match ir, ir' with
  | ÔčĘs, dÔčę, ÔčĘ_, d'Ôčę =>
      Eq.rec (motive := ExtMotive I O s d) (fun _ ÔćŽ mk_congr I O s) eq1 d' eq2

/-- The converse of `IR.ext`: an equality in `IR` determines a
pointwise equality of directions (transported along the shape equality
induced by the first projection). -/
theorem snd_eq_of_eq {ir ir' : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O} :
    (eq : ir = ir') Ôćĺ ir.2 = ir'.2 Ôłś directionOfEq I O (congrArg (fun t ÔćŽ t.1) eq)
  | rfl => rfl

/-- The eliminator (the algebra morphism from the initial algebra) for
`IR`, taking the algebra in morphism form. -/
def elim.{v} (V : Type v) (alg : Obj.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V Ôćĺ V) : IR I O Ôćĺ V :=
  WType.elim.{max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI, v} V alg

/-- The eliminator for `IR`, taking the algebra in the `IR.Alg` form. -/
def elimAlg.{v} (V : Type v) (alg : Alg.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O V) : IR I O Ôćĺ V :=
  elim I O V (Alg.toHom I O V alg)

/-- The type of the step argument of `IR`'s recursors at a
`Sort`-valued motive: from a shape, a subcode assignment, and results
for the subcodes, produce the result for the constructed code. The
result sort (an `imax` expression) is left to inference; the
specializations `IR.RecStep` and `IR.InductionStep` carry the explicit
ascriptions. -/
def Step.{v} (motive : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O Ôćĺ Sort v) :=
  (a : Shape O) Ôćĺ (f : Direction I O a Ôćĺ IR I O) Ôćĺ
  ((d : Direction I O a) Ôćĺ motive (f d)) Ôćĺ motive (mk I O a f)

/-- The step argument type at a `Type`-valued motive (for `IR.rec`,
`IR.sigmaRec`, and their companions). -/
def RecStep.{v} (motive : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O Ôćĺ Type v) :
    Type (max (uA + 1) uI uO v) :=
  Step I O motive

/-- The step argument type at a `Prop`-valued motive (for `IR.induction`). -/
def InductionStep (motive : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O Ôćĺ Prop) : Prop :=
  Step I O motive

/-- The induction principle ÔÇö the recursor restricted to `Prop`-valued
motives. (The compiler does not generate code for `WType.rec`
applications, so `WType.rec` is used only here, where propositions
need no code.) -/
theorem induction (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Prop) :
    InductionStep.{uA, uI, uO} I O motive Ôćĺ ÔłÇ t : IR I O, motive t :=
  WType.rec.{0, max (uA + 1) uO, max uA uI}
    (╬▒ := Shape O) (╬▓ := Direction I O) (motive := motive)

/-- The `IR.pFunctor` algebra over a sigma type generated by a
recursor step. -/
def sigmaRecAlg.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) :
    Obj I O (╬ú e, motive e) Ôćĺ ╬ú e, motive e :=
  fun ÔčĘs, fÔčę ÔćŽ
    ÔčĘmk I O s (Sigma.fst Ôłś f), mk' s (Sigma.fst Ôłś f) (fun d ÔćŽ (f d).2)Ôčę

/-- `IR.sigmaRecAlg` preserves the shape component. -/
theorem sigmaRecAlg_fst_fst.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) (t : Obj I O (╬ú e, motive e)) :
    (sigmaRecAlg I O motive mk' t).1.1 = t.1 :=
  rfl

/-- `IR.sigmaRecAlg` preserves the direction component. -/
theorem sigmaRecAlg_fst_snd.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) (t : Obj I O (╬ú e, motive e)) :
    (sigmaRecAlg I O motive mk' t).1.2 = Sigma.fst Ôłś t.2 :=
  rfl

/-- The recursor's auxiliary fold into a sigma type. -/
def sigmaRec.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) : IR I O Ôćĺ ╬ú e, motive e :=
  elim I O (╬ú e, motive e) (sigmaRecAlg I O motive mk')

/-- The inductive step of the proof that `IR.sigmaRec` is a section of
the first projection. -/
theorem sigmaRec_fst_step.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) :
    InductionStep.{uA, uI, uO} I O (fun t ÔćŽ (sigmaRec I O motive mk' t).1 = t) :=
  fun _ _ ih ÔćŽ ext I O rfl (funext ih)

/-- `IR.sigmaRec` is a section of the first projection. -/
theorem sigmaRec_fst.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) :
    ÔłÇ t : IR I O, (sigmaRec I O motive mk' t).1 = t :=
  induction I O (motive := fun t ÔćŽ (sigmaRec I O motive mk' t).1 = t)
    (sigmaRec_fst_step I O motive mk')

/-- The shape component of `IR.sigmaRec` agrees with the shape
component of the argument. -/
theorem sigmaRec_fst_fst.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) (t : IR I O) :
    (sigmaRec I O motive mk' t).1.1 = t.1 :=
  match t with
  | ÔčĘ_, _Ôčę => rfl

/-- The direction component of `IR.sigmaRec` agrees with the direction
component of the argument, transported along `IR.sigmaRec_fst_fst`. -/
theorem sigmaRec_fst_snd.{v} (motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v)
    (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) (t : IR I O) :
    (sigmaRec I O motive mk' t).1.2 =
      t.2 Ôłś directionOfEq I O (sigmaRec_fst_fst I O motive mk' t) :=
  snd_eq_of_eq I O (sigmaRec_fst I O motive mk' t)

/-- The recursor ÔÇö the dependent eliminator for `IR`. -/
def rec.{v} {motive : IR I O Ôćĺ Type v} (mk' : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, v} I O motive) :
    (t : IR I O) Ôćĺ motive t :=
  sigmaFstSectionElim (sigmaRec I O motive mk') (sigmaRec_fst I O motive mk')

end IR

namespace IR

/-- The constant (`iota`) case of the interpretation of an `IR` code
as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`: the constant object map at the
singleton family decoding to `o`. -/
def interpObjIota (o : O) : FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O :=
  fun _ ÔćŽ ÔčĘULift Unit, fun _ ÔćŽ oÔčę

/-- The dependent sum (`sigma`) case of the interpretation of an `IR`
code as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`: the pointwise indexed coproduct
over `A` of the interpretations `╬▒` of the subcodes. -/
def interpObjSigma (A : Type uA)
    (╬▒ : A Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O) :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O :=
  fun X ÔćŽ FreeCoprodCompDisc.coprod.{uA, uO, uA} O A (fun a ÔćŽ ╬▒ a X)

/-- The dependent product (`delta`) case of the interpretation of an
`IR` code as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`: at an object `X`, the
indexed coproduct over `A Ôćĺ X.1` of the interpretations `╬▒` of the
subcodes at the directions induced by `X`. -/
def interpObjDelta (A : Type uA)
    (╬▒ : (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O) :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O :=
  fun X ÔćŽ
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.coprod.{uA, uO, uA} O (A Ôćĺ X.1) (fun g ÔćŽ ╬▒ (X.2 Ôłś g) X)

/-- The algebra which computes one step of the interpretation of an
`IR` code as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`. -/
def interpObjAlg :
    Alg.{uA, uI, uO, max (uA + 1) uI uO} I O
      (FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O) :=
  ÔčĘinterpObjIota I O, interpObjSigma I O, interpObjDelta I OÔčę

/-- The object map of the interpretation of an `IR` code as a
`FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`. -/
def interpObj : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O :=
  elimAlg I O (FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O) (interpObjAlg I O)

/-- The signature of the morphism map accompanying `IR.interpObj`. -/
def MorMapSig (ir : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O) : Type (max (uA + 1) uI) :=
  FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (interpObj I O ir)

/-- The morphism-map component of the constant (`iota`) interpretation
`IR.interpObjIota`: every morphism maps to the identity. -/
def interpMorIota (o : O) :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (interpObjIota.{uA, uI, uO} I O o) :=
  fun _ _ _ ÔćŽ ÔčĘid, rflÔčę

/-- The morphism-map component of the dependent sum (`sigma`)
interpretation `IR.interpObjSigma`: the indexed coproduct of the
componentwise morphism maps `╬╝`. -/
def interpMorSigma (A : Type uA)
    (╬▒ : A Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O)
    (╬╝ : (a : A) Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (╬▒ a)) :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (interpObjSigma I O A ╬▒) :=
  fun X Y h ÔćŽ
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.coprodMor O A A id
      (fun a ÔćŽ ╬▒ a X)
      (fun a ÔćŽ ╬▒ a Y)
      (fun a ÔćŽ ╬╝ a X Y h)

/-- The morphism-map component of the dependent product (`delta`)
interpretation `IR.interpObjDelta`: reindex along postcomposition with
the morphism, transporting each componentwise morphism map `╬╝` along
the morphism's commutation equality. -/
def interpMorDelta (A : Type uA)
    (╬▒ : (A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map.{uA, uI, uO} I O)
    (╬╝ : (f : A Ôćĺ I) Ôćĺ FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (╬▒ f)) :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.MapMor I O (interpObjDelta I O A ╬▒) :=
  fun X Y h ÔćŽ
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.coprodMor O (A Ôćĺ X.1) (A Ôćĺ Y.1) (fun g ÔćŽ h.1 Ôłś g)
      (fun g ÔćŽ ╬▒ (X.2 Ôłś g) X)
      (fun g ÔćŽ ╬▒ (Y.2 Ôłś g) Y)
      (fun g ÔćŽ
        FreeCoprodCompDisc.homOfEq O
          (congrArg (fun t ÔćŽ ╬▒ (t Ôłś g) Y) h.2.symm)
          (╬╝ (X.2 Ôłś g) X Y h))

/-- The step argument to the recursor which generates the morphism map
of the interpretation of an `IR` code as a `FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map`
(the object map is `IR.interpObj`). -/
def interpMorStep : RecStep.{uA, uI, uO, max (uA + 1) uI} I O (MorMapSig I O) :=
  fun s c m ÔćŽ match s with
  | Sum.inl o => interpMorIota I O o
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inl A) =>
      interpMorSigma I O A
        (fun a ÔćŽ interpObj I O (c (ULift.up a)))
        (fun a ÔćŽ m (ULift.up a))
  | Sum.inr (Sum.inr A) =>
      interpMorDelta I O A
        (fun f ÔćŽ interpObj I O (c f))
        m

/-- The morphism map of the interpretation of an `IR` code as a
`FreeCoprodCompDisc.Map` (the object map is `IR.interpObj`). -/
def interpMor (ir : IR.{uA, uI, uO} I O) : MorMapSig I O ir :=
  rec I O (interpMorStep I O) ir

end IR

section Universes

/-! ### Universes closed under dependent sums and products

The code of the universe generated by an arbitrary family of starting
types and closed under dependent sums and dependent products,
combining Examples 2.5 and 2.6 of
[GhaniNordvallForsbergMalatesta2015]: the coproduct of one `iota`
code per starting type (in place of the examples' single `iota` code
for the natural numbers), one dependent-sum former, and one
dependent-product former. The universe is an endofunctor example
(`IR I I`), so the input and output index types coincide.
-/

universe uK uT

/-- The binder-former subcode shared by `univSigma` and `univPi`: one
recursive argument (the type bound by the binder), then recursive
arguments indexed by its decoding (the family of types under the
binder), decoding to `former` applied to the decodings. -/
def univBinder.{v} (former : (X : Type v) Ôćĺ (X Ôćĺ Type v) Ôćĺ Type v) :
    IR.{v, v + 1, v + 1} (Type v) (Type v) :=
  IR.delta (Type v) (Type v) PUnit.{v + 1} (fun f ÔćŽ
    IR.delta (Type v) (Type v) (f PUnit.unit) (fun q ÔćŽ
      IR.iota (Type v) (Type v) (former (f PUnit.unit) q)))

/-- The dependent-sum-former subcode of a universe code. -/
def univSigma.{v} : IR.{v, v + 1, v + 1} (Type v) (Type v) :=
  univBinder (fun X q ÔćŽ ╬ú x : X, q x)

/-- The dependent-product-former subcode of a universe code. -/
def univPi.{v} : IR.{v, v + 1, v + 1} (Type v) (Type v) :=
  univBinder (fun X q ÔćŽ (x : X) Ôćĺ q x)

variable (K : Type uK) (T : K Ôćĺ Type uT)

/-- The starting-type subcode of a universe code: an `iota` code
decoding to the lifted starting type selected by `k`. -/
def univIota (k : K) :
    IR.{max uK uT, max uK uT + 1, max uK uT + 1}
      (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) :=
  IR.iota (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) (ULift.{uK} (T k))

/-- The constructors of the universe generated by a family of starting
types: one nullary constructor per starting type, a dependent-sum
former, and a dependent-product former. -/
def UnivConstructor : Type (max uK uT) :=
  K ÔŐĽ PUnit.{max uK uT + 1} ÔŐĽ PUnit.{max uK uT + 1}

/-- The subcode of the universe code selected by each constructor. -/
def univConstructorCode :
    UnivConstructor.{uK, uT} K Ôćĺ
      IR.{max uK uT, max uK uT + 1, max uK uT + 1}
        (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) :=
  Sum.elim (univIota K T)
    (Sum.elim (fun _ ÔćŽ univSigma.{max uK uT}) (fun _ ÔćŽ univPi.{max uK uT}))

/-- The code of the universe generated by the starting types `T`: the
coproduct, over `UnivConstructor`, of the subcodes. The universe
itself ÔÇö containing the (lifted) starting types and closed under
dependent sums and dependent products ÔÇö is the initial algebra of the
code's interpretation; this file provides the code and the
interpretation, not the initial algebra. -/
def univCode :
    IR.{max uK uT, max uK uT + 1, max uK uT + 1}
      (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) :=
  IR.sigma (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) (UnivConstructor.{uK, uT} K)
    (fun i ÔćŽ univConstructorCode K T i.down)

/-- The object map of the interpretation of `univCode`. -/
def univEndo :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.Endo.{max uK uT, max uK uT + 1} (Type (max uK uT)) :=
  IR.interpObj (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) (univCode K T)

/-- The morphism map of the interpretation of `univCode` (the object
map is `univEndo`). -/
def univEndoMor :
    FreeCoprodCompDisc.EndoMor (Type (max uK uT)) (univEndo K T) :=
  IR.interpMor (Type (max uK uT)) (Type (max uK uT)) (univCode K T)

end Universes

end IndRec
